  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOPT / PARC Gaza: Climate and Resource Resilience</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">46 farmers will be participate in structural and farming resilience training, after which they will be supported with the rehabilitation of their farms according to build back better standards and the installation of rainwater harvesting units to improve sustainability of water management.

6 Community Based Organisation representatives, 8 Local Committee Members and 20 community members will also participate in the training and 20 community members will be engaged in cash for work to support with the installation of the rainwater harvesting units for the farms.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community resilience will be increased through capacity strengthening of farmers, who will have sustainable solutions for the impact of climate change on their structures and resources, as well as CBOs and community committees, who will be engaged to encourage further initiatives within the community. Selected community members will benefit from capacity strengthening which they may be able to utilise to seek job opportunities.</narrative>
  </description>
